THE gogo of two girls who died when a scholar transport van rolled over them is struggling to come to terms with her loss. Cousins Ayanda Maseko (11) and Xolile Khuzwayo (13), pupils at Otimati Primary School in Maphumulo, northern KZN, died on Tuesday, 24 January. Their gogo, Qondephi Khuzwayo (64), said the accident happened at the first school the driver stopped at in the morning. “We were told by a survivor that the driver stopped the van and got out to open the school gate. When he came to open the back, the van started rolling,” she said. REGISTER TO COMMENT! “He tried to stop the van but couldn’t. The kids panicked and got out of the van, and it rolled over them. My grandchildren died and two others were injured.” She said the child told them the van was parked on a steep hill, which was probably why it rolled. “The driver came to speak to us. He was in great shock and couldn’t even speak,” she said. KZN police spokeswoman Lieutenant-Colonel Nqobile Gwala said a case of culpable homicide is being investigated by Maphumulo cop shop after pupils died in an accident at Otimati area.